This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification and adversarial examples. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a defense framework based on a multi-label classification model. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a data-driven approach to improve the robustness of CNN models. The paper also deals with security and cryptography (cs.CR) as it addresses the issue of adversarial attacks on CNNs. Finally, it involves neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as it proposes a framework based on convolutional neural networks.
